---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ToolPageCta from '../../components/ToolPageCta.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';
import AdUnit from '../../components/AdUnit.astro';

const faq = [
  {
    question: "What is the main difference between Pulumi and Terraform?",
    answer: "The fundamental difference is the language model. Terraform uses HCL (HashiCorp Configuration Language), a declarative DSL purpose-built for infrastructure — readable but limited in expressiveness. Pulumi lets you write infrastructure in general-purpose languages like TypeScript, Python, Go, C#, and Java, meaning you get loops, conditionals, functions, classes, and the full power of your existing language ecosystem. Both tools are declarative in intent (you describe desired state), but Pulumi expresses that state in real code rather than configuration files. This makes Pulumi especially powerful for teams with complex, dynamic infrastructure requirements, while Terraform's HCL remains simpler for straightforward, static configurations."
  },
  {
    question: "Which IaC tool should I choose for a new project in 2026?",
    answer: "For most greenfield projects, the decision comes down to two factors: team language preference and existing ecosystem. If your team is already strong in TypeScript or Python and you want type safety, reusable component libraries, and unit-testable infrastructure code, Pulumi is the better choice. If your team has no strong language preference, is hiring ops-focused engineers who know HCL, or needs to integrate with a large Terraform provider ecosystem (1,000+ providers via the Terraform Registry), Terraform (or OpenTofu) is the safer default. In 2026, both tools are production-mature. The real question is whether you want infrastructure-as-code or infrastructure-as-configuration."
  },
  {
    question: "Is Pulumi compatible with Terraform providers?",
    answer: "Yes. Pulumi has a bridge layer (pulumi-terraform-bridge) that wraps most Terraform providers and makes them usable in Pulumi programs. This means the 1,000+ providers available in the Terraform Registry — AWS, Azure, GCP, Datadog, Cloudflare, and virtually every SaaS tool — are accessible from Pulumi code. Pulumi also has its own native providers (AWS Native, Azure Native, Kubernetes) generated directly from cloud provider API specs, which are typically more complete and up-to-date than Terraform's equivalents. So Pulumi has full provider coverage without sacrificing compatibility."
  },
  {
    question: "How does state management differ between Pulumi and Terraform?",
    answer: "Both tools store infrastructure state as a snapshot of your deployed resources. Terraform stores state in a flat JSON file (terraform.tfstate), which you must manage yourself — typically by pushing it to remote backends like S3+DynamoDB, GCS, or Terraform Cloud. Pulumi stores state either in Pulumi Cloud (hosted, free tier available) or in self-managed backends (S3, Azure Blob, GCS, local filesystem). Pulumi Cloud provides additional features like deployment history, drift detection UI, audit logs, and team access controls built in. With Terraform, those features require Terraform Cloud/Enterprise or custom tooling. For teams that want zero state management overhead, Pulumi Cloud has a clear advantage."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I migrate from Terraform to Pulumi without rewriting everything?",
    answer: "Yes — Pulumi provides a conversion tool (pulumi convert --from terraform) that translates HCL into your target language (TypeScript, Python, Go, or C#). For existing infrastructure, Pulumi's import command (pulumi import) reads live cloud resources and generates both the state entry and the corresponding code, so you don't need to recreate resources. The migration path is typically: (1) convert HCL to Pulumi code using the converter, (2) import existing state using pulumi state import or a batch import script, (3) run pulumi preview to verify no unintended changes, (4) gradually migrate stacks team by team. Most teams complete a full migration in 2–8 weeks depending on stack complexity."
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Pulumi vs Terraform: IaC Comparison Tool 2026"
  description="Interactive comparison of Pulumi vs Terraform. Side-by-side feature table, use case recommender, code examples in HCL and TypeScript/Python, and migration guide."
  tool="Pulumi vs Terraform, IaC comparison, infrastructure as code, Terraform HCL, Pulumi TypeScript, state management, cloud provisioning"
  faq={faq}
>
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Pulumi vs Terraform</h1>
  <p class="text-text-muted mb-4">Interactive infrastructure-as-code comparison. Filter features by category, get a personalized recommendation, compare real code examples, and find your migration path.</p>

  <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 text-sm text-text-muted flex-wrap">
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> 10-category feature table with winners</span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Use case recommender</span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Code comparison (HCL vs TypeScript/Python)</span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Migration path guide</span>
  </div>

  <!-- Feature Comparison Table -->
  <div class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-xl p-5 mb-6">
    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-between gap-3 mb-4">
      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold">Feature Comparison</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2" id="category-filters">
        <button class="filter-btn active text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded-lg border border-primary bg-primary/10 text-primary transition-colors" data-cat="all">All</button>
        <button class="filter-btn text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded-lg border border-border hover:border-primary transition-colors" data-cat="language">Language</button>
        <button class="filter-btn text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded-lg border border-border hover:border-primary transition-colors" data-cat="state">State</button>
        <button class="filter-btn text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded-lg border border-border hover:border-primary transition-colors" data-cat="ecosystem">Ecosystem</button>
        <button class="filter-btn text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded-lg border border-border hover:border-primary transition-colors" data-cat="ops">Ops</button>
        <button class="filter-btn text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded-lg border border-border hover:border-primary transition-colors" data-cat="testing">Testing</button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm min-w-[620px]" id="comparison-table">
        <thead>
          <tr class="text-text-muted text-xs border-b border-border">
            <th class="text-left pb-3 font-medium w-44">Category / Feature</th>
            <th class="text-center pb-3 font-medium w-36">
              <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5">
                <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-blue-500 inline-block"></span>Pulumi
              </span>
            </th>
            <th class="text-center pb-3 font-medium w-36">
              <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5">
                <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-purple-500 inline-block"></span>Terraform
              </span>
            </th>
            <th class="text-center pb-3 font-medium w-24">Winner</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-border text-xs" id="table-body">
          <!-- Language support -->
          <tr data-cat="language">
            <td class="py-3 font-medium">Language support</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center">TypeScript, Python, Go, C#, Java</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center">HCL (proprietary DSL)</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center"><span class="winner-badge pulumi">Pulumi</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr data-cat="language">
            <td class="py-3 font-medium">Learning curve</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center text-yellow-500">Medium — need a real lang</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center text-green-500">Low — HCL is simple</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center"><span class="winner-badge terraform">Terraform</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr data-cat="language">
            <td class="py-3 font-medium">IDE support / autocomplete</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center text-green-500">Full (TS/Python LSP)</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center text-yellow-500">HCL plugins (limited)</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center"><span class="winner-badge pulumi">Pulumi</span></td>
          </tr>
          <!-- State management -->
          <tr data-cat="state">
            <td class="py-3 font-medium">State management</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center">Pulumi Cloud or self-managed backends</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center">terraform.tfstate + remote backends</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center"><span class="winner-badge tie">Tie</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr data-cat="state">
            <td class="py-3 font-medium">Drift detection</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center text-green-500">Built-in (Pulumi Cloud UI)</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center text-yellow-500">terraform plan (manual)</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center"><span class="winner-badge pulumi">Pulumi</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr data-cat="state">
            <td class="py-3 font-medium">Stack references</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center text-green-500">Native StackReference type</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center text-yellow-500">terraform_remote_state</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center"><span class="winner-badge pulumi">Pulumi</span></td>
          </tr>
          <!-- Ecosystem -->
          <tr data-cat="ecosystem">
            <td class="py-3 font-medium">Provider ecosystem</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center">1,000+ (via TF bridge + native)</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center text-green-500">1,000+ (Terraform Registry)</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center"><span class="winner-badge tie">Tie</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr data-cat="ecosystem">
            <td class="py-3 font-medium">Cloud coverage</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center">AWS, Azure, GCP + 100s more</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center text-green-500">AWS, Azure, GCP + 100s more</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center"><span class="winner-badge tie">Tie</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr data-cat="ecosystem">
            <td class="py-3 font-medium">Import existing resources</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center text-green-500">pulumi import (generates code)</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center text-yellow-500">terraform import (no codegen)</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center"><span class="winner-badge pulumi">Pulumi</span></td>
          </tr>
          <!-- Ops -->
          <tr data-cat="ops">
            <td class="py-3 font-medium">Pricing / OSS</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center text-green-500">OSS + free Pulumi Cloud tier</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center text-yellow-500">BSL license (v1.6+), OpenTofu fork</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center"><span class="winner-badge pulumi">Pulumi</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr data-cat="ops">
            <td class="py-3 font-medium">CI/CD integrations</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center">GitHub Actions, GitLab, Jenkins…</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center">GitHub Actions, GitLab, Jenkins…</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center"><span class="winner-badge tie">Tie</span></td>
          </tr>
          <!-- Testing -->
          <tr data-cat="testing">
            <td class="py-3 font-medium">Testing support</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center text-green-500">Unit tests (Jest, pytest), mocking</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center text-yellow-500">terratest (Go), limited</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center"><span class="winner-badge pulumi">Pulumi</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr data-cat="testing">
            <td class="py-3 font-medium">Policy as code</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center text-green-500">CrossGuard (TypeScript/Python)</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center">Sentinel / OPA (paid / external)</td>
            <td class="py-3 text-center"><span class="winner-badge pulumi">Pulumi</span></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-4 flex items-center gap-4 text-xs text-text-muted">
      <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="winner-badge pulumi inline-block">Pulumi</span> Pulumi wins</span>
      <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="winner-badge terraform inline-block">Terraform</span> Terraform wins</span>
      <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="winner-badge tie inline-block">Tie</span> Roughly equal</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <AdUnit slot="auto" format="auto" label="Advertisement" />

  <!-- Use Case Recommender -->
  <div class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-xl p-5 mb-6">
    <h2 class="text-base font-semibold mb-1">Use Case Recommender</h2>
    <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mb-4">Select all that apply. The tool will recommend Pulumi or Terraform based on your situation.</p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-2 mb-5" id="recommender-checks">
      <label class="recommender-item flex items-start gap-2.5 p-3 rounded-lg border border-border hover:border-primary cursor-pointer transition-colors">
        <input type="checkbox" class="rec-check mt-0.5 accent-primary" data-score-pulumi="2" data-score-tf="0" />
        <span class="text-xs">Strong TypeScript or Python team</span>
      </label>
      <label class="recommender-item flex items-start gap-2.5 p-3 rounded-lg border border-border hover:border-primary cursor-pointer transition-colors">
        <input type="checkbox" class="rec-check mt-0.5 accent-primary" data-score-pulumi="0" data-score-tf="2" />
        <span class="text-xs">Ops team more comfortable with config files</span>
      </label>
      <label class="recommender-item flex items-start gap-2.5 p-3 rounded-lg border border-border hover:border-primary cursor-pointer transition-colors">
        <input type="checkbox" class="rec-check mt-0.5 accent-primary" data-score-pulumi="2" data-score-tf="0" />
        <span class="text-xs">Need unit tests for infrastructure code</span>
      </label>
      <label class="recommender-item flex items-start gap-2.5 p-3 rounded-lg border border-border hover:border-primary cursor-pointer transition-colors">
        <input type="checkbox" class="rec-check mt-0.5 accent-primary" data-score-pulumi="0" data-score-tf="2" />
        <span class="text-xs">Large existing Terraform codebase</span>
      </label>
      <label class="recommender-item flex items-start gap-2.5 p-3 rounded-lg border border-border hover:border-primary cursor-pointer transition-colors">
        <input type="checkbox" class="rec-check mt-0.5 accent-primary" data-score-pulumi="1" data-score-tf="1" />
        <span class="text-xs">Multi-cloud deployment (AWS + GCP + Azure)</span>
      </label>
      <label class="recommender-item flex items-start gap-2.5 p-3 rounded-lg border border-border hover:border-primary cursor-pointer transition-colors">
        <input type="checkbox" class="rec-check mt-0.5 accent-primary" data-score-pulumi="2" data-score-tf="0" />
        <span class="text-xs">Dynamic/programmatic infra (loops, conditions)</span>
      </label>
      <label class="recommender-item flex items-start gap-2.5 p-3 rounded-lg border border-border hover:border-primary cursor-pointer transition-colors">
        <input type="checkbox" class="rec-check mt-0.5 accent-primary" data-score-pulumi="0" data-score-tf="2" />
        <span class="text-xs">Hiring open-source Terraform talent</span>
      </label>
      <label class="recommender-item flex items-start gap-2.5 p-3 rounded-lg border border-border hover:border-primary cursor-pointer transition-colors">
        <input type="checkbox" class="rec-check mt-0.5 accent-primary" data-score-pulumi="1" data-score-tf="0" />
        <span class="text-xs">Want built-in drift detection dashboard</span>
      </label>
      <label class="recommender-item flex items-start gap-2.5 p-3 rounded-lg border border-border hover:border-primary cursor-pointer transition-colors">
        <input type="checkbox" class="rec-check mt-0.5 accent-primary" data-score-pulumi="0" data-score-tf="1" />
        <span class="text-xs">Need maximum provider ecosystem (1,000+ providers)</span>
      </label>
      <label class="recommender-item flex items-start gap-2.5 p-3 rounded-lg border border-border hover:border-primary cursor-pointer transition-colors">
        <input type="checkbox" class="rec-check mt-0.5 accent-primary" data-score-pulumi="2" data-score-tf="0" />
        <span class="text-xs">Building reusable infra component libraries</span>
      </label>
    </div>

    <div id="rec-result" class="hidden rounded-xl p-4 border">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
        <span class="text-base font-bold" id="rec-tool-name"></span>
        <span class="text-xs text-text-muted" id="rec-score-label"></span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-text-muted" id="rec-reason"></p>
      <div class="mt-3 flex gap-3">
        <div class="flex-1 text-center">
          <div class="text-lg font-bold text-blue-500" id="rec-pulumi-score">0</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-text-muted">Pulumi score</div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1 text-center">
          <div class="text-lg font-bold text-purple-500" id="rec-tf-score">0</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-text-muted">Terraform score</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Code Comparison -->
  <div class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-xl p-5 mb-6">
    <h2 class="text-base font-semibold mb-1">Code Comparison</h2>
    <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mb-4">Same infrastructure, different languages. Switch between examples.</p>

    <div class="flex gap-2 mb-4" id="code-tabs">
      <button class="code-tab-btn active text-xs px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg border border-primary bg-primary/10 text-primary transition-colors" data-example="s3">S3 Bucket (AWS)</button>
      <button class="code-tab-btn text-xs px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg border border-border hover:border-primary transition-colors" data-example="gcs">GCS Bucket (GCP)</button>
      <button class="code-tab-btn text-xs px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg border border-border hover:border-primary transition-colors" data-example="k8s">Kubernetes Deployment</button>
    </div>

    <div id="code-examples">
      <!-- S3 -->
      <div class="code-example" data-example="s3">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
              <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-400">Pulumi — TypeScript</span>
              <button class="copy-btn text-xs text-text-muted hover:text-primary transition-colors" data-target="pulumi-s3-ts">Copy</button>
            </div>
            <pre class="bg-bg rounded-lg border border-border p-4 text-xs overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed" id="pulumi-s3-ts"><code><span class="text-purple-400">import</span> <span class="text-white">* as aws</span> <span class="text-purple-400">from</span> <span class="text-green-400">"@pulumi/aws"</span><span class="text-text-muted">;</span>

<span class="text-blue-400">const</span> <span class="text-white">bucket</span> <span class="text-text-muted">=</span> <span class="text-blue-400">new</span> <span class="text-yellow-400">aws.s3.BucketV2</span><span class="text-text-muted">(</span><span class="text-green-400">"my-bucket"</span><span class="text-text-muted">, {</span>
  <span class="text-white">bucket</span><span class="text-text-muted">:</span> <span class="text-green-400">"my-app-assets"</span><span class="text-text-muted">,</span>
  <span class="text-white">tags</span><span class="text-text-muted">: {</span>
    <span class="text-white">Environment</span><span class="text-text-muted">:</span> <span class="text-green-400">"production"</span><span class="text-text-muted">,</span>
    <span class="text-white">Team</span><span class="text-text-muted">:</span> <span class="text-green-400">"platform"</span><span class="text-text-muted">,</span>
  <span class="text-text-muted">},</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">});</span>

<span class="text-blue-400">new</span> <span class="text-yellow-400">aws.s3.BucketVersioningV2</span><span class="text-text-muted">(</span><span class="text-green-400">"versioning"</span><span class="text-text-muted">, {</span>
  <span class="text-white">bucket</span><span class="text-text-muted">:</span> <span class="text-white">bucket.id</span><span class="text-text-muted">,</span>
  <span class="text-white">versioningConfiguration</span><span class="text-text-muted">: {</span>
    <span class="text-white">status</span><span class="text-text-muted">:</span> <span class="text-green-400">"Enabled"</span><span class="text-text-muted">,</span>
  <span class="text-text-muted">},</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">});</span>

<span class="text-blue-400">export const</span> <span class="text-white">bucketName</span> <span class="text-text-muted">=</span> <span class="text-white">bucket.id</span><span class="text-text-muted">;</span>
<span class="text-blue-400">export const</span> <span class="text-white">bucketArn</span> <span class="text-text-muted">=</span> <span class="text-white">bucket.arn</span><span class="text-text-muted">;</span></code></pre>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
              <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-purple-400">Terraform — HCL</span>
              <button class="copy-btn text-xs text-text-muted hover:text-primary transition-colors" data-target="tf-s3-hcl">Copy</button>
            </div>
            <pre class="bg-bg rounded-lg border border-border p-4 text-xs overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed" id="tf-s3-hcl"><code><span class="text-blue-400">resource</span> <span class="text-green-400">"aws_s3_bucket"</span> <span class="text-green-400">"my_bucket"</span> <span class="text-text-muted">{</span>
  <span class="text-white">bucket</span> <span class="text-text-muted">=</span> <span class="text-green-400">"my-app-assets"</span>

  <span class="text-white">tags</span> <span class="text-text-muted">= {</span>
    <span class="text-white">Environment</span> <span class="text-text-muted">=</span> <span class="text-green-400">"production"</span>
    <span class="text-white">Team</span>        <span class="text-text-muted">=</span> <span class="text-green-400">"platform"</span>
  <span class="text-text-muted">}</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">}</span>

<span class="text-blue-400">resource</span> <span class="text-green-400">"aws_s3_bucket_versioning"</span> <span class="text-green-400">"versioning"</span> <span class="text-text-muted">{</span>
  <span class="text-white">bucket</span> <span class="text-text-muted">=</span> <span class="text-white">aws_s3_bucket.my_bucket.id</span>

  <span class="text-white">versioning_configuration</span> <span class="text-text-muted">{</span>
    <span class="text-white">status</span> <span class="text-text-muted">=</span> <span class="text-green-400">"Enabled"</span>
  <span class="text-text-muted">}</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">}</span>

<span class="text-blue-400">output</span> <span class="text-green-400">"bucket_name"</span> <span class="text-text-muted">{</span>
  <span class="text-white">value</span> <span class="text-text-muted">=</span> <span class="text-white">aws_s3_bucket.my_bucket.id</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">}</span>
<span class="text-blue-400">output</span> <span class="text-green-400">"bucket_arn"</span> <span class="text-text-muted">{</span>
  <span class="text-white">value</span> <span class="text-text-muted">=</span> <span class="text-white">aws_s3_bucket.my_bucket.arn</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">}</span></code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-3 grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
              <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-400">Pulumi — Python</span>
              <button class="copy-btn text-xs text-text-muted hover:text-primary transition-colors" data-target="pulumi-s3-py">Copy</button>
            </div>
            <pre class="bg-bg rounded-lg border border-border p-4 text-xs overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed" id="pulumi-s3-py"><code><span class="text-purple-400">import</span> <span class="text-white">pulumi_aws</span> <span class="text-purple-400">as</span> <span class="text-white">aws</span>

<span class="text-white">bucket</span> <span class="text-text-muted">=</span> <span class="text-yellow-400">aws.s3.BucketV2</span><span class="text-text-muted">(</span><span class="text-green-400">"my-bucket"</span><span class="text-text-muted">,</span>
