  <!-- Migration Path -->
  <div class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-xl p-5 mb-6">
    <h2 class="text-base font-semibold mb-4">Migration Path: Terraform → Pulumi</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <div class="flex gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-border">
        <div class="w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-blue-500/10 border border-blue-500/30 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 text-blue-400 text-xs font-bold">1</div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold mb-0.5">Convert HCL to Pulumi code</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-muted">Run <code class="bg-bg px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-blue-300">pulumi convert --from terraform --language typescript</code> in your Terraform root. The converter generates equivalent Pulumi TypeScript (or Python/Go). Review and clean up generated code — it's not always perfect for complex modules.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-border">
        <div class="w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-blue-500/10 border border-blue-500/30 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 text-blue-400 text-xs font-bold">2</div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold mb-0.5">Import existing state</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-muted">Use <code class="bg-bg px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-blue-300">pulumi import &lt;type&gt; &lt;name&gt; &lt;id&gt;</code> for each resource, or write a bulk import script from your <code class="bg-bg px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-blue-300">terraform.tfstate</code>. Pulumi generates the corresponding resource code alongside the state entry.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-border">
        <div class="w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-blue-500/10 border border-blue-500/30 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 text-blue-400 text-xs font-bold">3</div>
