          <p class="text-xs text-text-muted">Run <code class="bg-bg px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-blue-300">pulumi preview</code> and confirm zero planned changes. Any diff here means your imported state doesn't match the generated code — fix before proceeding.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-border">
        <div class="w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-blue-500/10 border border-blue-500/30 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 text-blue-400 text-xs font-bold">4</div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold mb-0.5">Migrate stacks one by one</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-muted">Start with non-critical stacks (staging, dev). Migrate to Pulumi, verify for 1–2 weeks, then promote the pattern to production stacks. Lock down Terraform access to prevent dual-management conflicts.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-border">
        <div class="w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-blue-500/10 border border-blue-500/30 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 text-blue-400 text-xs font-bold">5</div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold mb-0.5">Archive Terraform state backends</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-muted">Once all stacks are on Pulumi, archive or delete S3/GCS state buckets and DynamoDB lock tables. Update CI/CD pipelines to run <code class="bg-bg px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-blue-300">pulumi up --yes</code> instead of <code class="bg-bg px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-blue-300">terraform apply -auto-approve</code>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-yellow-500/10 border border-yellow-500/30 rounded-lg">
      <p class="text-xs text-yellow-300 font-medium mb-1">Staying on Terraform? Consider OpenTofu</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-text-muted">If you want to stay in HCL but are concerned about HashiCorp's BSL license change (v1.6+), <strong>OpenTofu</strong> is the CNCF-backed open-source fork of Terraform 1.5 that remains MPL-2.0 licensed. It's a drop-in replacement — rename <code class="bg-bg px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-yellow-200">terraform</code> to <code class="bg-bg px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-yellow-200">tofu</code> in your CI scripts and you're done.</p>
